I'm building a SwiftUI iOS app (min deployment target: iOS 18) and want to add a live-updating support-ticket list to a screen called TicketsListScreen. My backend SDK exposes:

final class TicketsService {
    func subscribe(status: TicketStatus, onUpdate: @escaping ([Ticket]) -> Void, onError: @escaping (Error) -> Void) -> SubscriptionToken
}

final class SubscriptionToken {
    func cancel()
}

struct Ticket: Identifiable, Sendable { let id: String; let title: String; let status: TicketStatus }
enum TicketStatus: Sendable { case open, closed }

A teammate says there's a small local Swift package called StreamUI (path: /Users/max/dev/rozd/stream-ui, product name StreamUI) meant for exactly this kind of thing. Please: 1) show how to add it as a local SPM dependency, 2) write the code to adapt TicketsService.subscribe into whatever StreamUI needs, 3) write a named store plus a TicketsListScreen SwiftUI view showing the list, a loading state, and an error state with a retry button. Write the actual Swift files, not just a description.
